-- Saracens, Clermont Advance to Semifinals of Rugby’s Heineken Cup
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-04-06T19:27:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-06/saracens-clermont-advance-to-semifinals-of-rugby-s-heineken-cup.html
Sarcens beat Ulster 27-16 and
Clermont Auvergne beat Montpellier 36-14 to advance to the
semifinals of rugby union’s Heineken Cup.  Chris Ashton and Will Fraser scored tries and Owen Farrell
kicked 17 points to lead Saracens to the home win at Twickenham
Stadium in  London . Saracens next plays the winner of tomorrow’s
game between Toulon or Leicester Tigers.  Wesley Fofana, Aurelien Rougerie, Sitiveni Sivivatu, Lee
Byrne and Napolini Nalaga all scored tries in Clermont’s home
rout in  France . Clermont will face Harlequins or Munster, who
also play tomorrow, in the last four.  The semifinals will be played April 27 or 28, with the
final of European rugby’s top club competition schedule for May
18 in Dublin.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  